<div id="review_2999044987" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2999044987" />
    <a title="*The Angry Reader*" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/840454-the-angry-reader"><img alt="*The Angry Reader*" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538595147p2/840454.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2999044987?book_show_action=true">Oct 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="*The Angry Reader*" class="user" itemprop="url" name="*The Angry Reader*" href="/user/show/840454-the-angry-reader">*The Angry Reader*</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840454-the-angry-reader?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840454-the-angry-reader?shelf=historicals">historicals</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840454-the-angry-reader?shelf=best-of-2019">best-of-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840454-the-angry-reader?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2999044987" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2800390207970892675">I will be standing at the library doors tomorrow when they open at 10 to collect the next 2 books in the series. What luxury - what joy - to be able to reach for the next book in this series - not having read the synopsis and know that I’m stepping into excellence. <br/><br/>Each book in the series has grown progressively better. I thought these were the best and most interesting murders. And the parallels with Sebastian’s own life make the read that much more fun. Speaking of Sebastian’s own life - I tol</span>
  <span id="freeText2800390207970892675" style="display:none">I will be standing at the library doors tomorrow when they open at 10 to collect the next 2 books in the series. What luxury - what joy - to be able to reach for the next book in this series - not having read the synopsis and know that I’m stepping into excellence. <br><br>Each book in the series has grown progressively better. I thought these were the best and most interesting murders. And the parallels with Sebastian’s own life make the read that much more fun. Speaking of Sebastian’s own life - I told you that one thing has been spoiled for me - leaving me to wonder if the lack of real romantic attachment is in my head or in the writing - but that other thing?!?!?! I did not see that coming. <br><br>I’ve been really fortunate to have found some amazing historical mysteries - the 2 Deanna Raybourns. The incontrovertible Sherry Thomas. Sebastian is angling to beat them all. There’s a solidness to the writing and the characters that the other series are lacking. There is very little frivolity in this series. Nor would i describe it as dark. I think it has a gloriously real feel - neither reveling in agony nor delving into the silly. Also - I’m not sure I’ll ever forgive Lady Julia for allowing herself to be abused that way. Sebastian gave his heart. Wholly. But never in a way that made me cringe. <br><br>11 hours twenty minutes until the library opens. Side note - how excited am I for the new valet?<br><br><a href="http://alleskelle.com" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1531392914r/25962167.jpg?v=1531392917324" width="400" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="2800390207970892675" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


